{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":943,"text":"I'm really glad to be here."},{"time":3015,"text":"I'm glad you're here,"},{"time":4727,"text":"because that would be a little weird."},{"time":7460,"text":"I'm glad we're all here."},{"time":10303,"text":"And by \"here,\" I don't mean here."},{"time":14831,"text":"Or here."},{"time":16728,"text":"But here."},{"time":17904,"text":"I mean Earth."},{"time":19627,"text":"And by \"we,\" I don't mean\nthose of us in this auditorium,"},{"time":23594,"text":"but life,"},{"time":25088,"text":"all life on Earth --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26561,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32280,"text":"from complex to single-celled,"},{"time":34295,"text":"from mold to mushrooms"},{"time":36643,"text":"to flying bears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38045,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41736,"text":"The interesting thing is,"},{"time":43269,"text":"Earth is the only place\nwe know of that has life --"},{"time":46324,"text":"8.7 million species."},{"time":48660,"text":"We've looked other places,"},{"time":49938,"text":"maybe not as hard\nas we should or we could,"},{"time":52059,"text":"but we've looked and haven't found any;"},{"time":54010,"text":"Earth is the only place\nwe know of with life."},{"time":57318,"text":"Is Earth special?"},{"time":59591,"text":"This is a question I've wanted\nto know the answer to"},{"time":62069,"text":"since I was a small child,"},{"time":63347,"text":"and I suspect 80 percent\nof this auditorium"},{"time":65403,"text":"has thought the same thing\nand also wanted to know the answer."},{"time":68879,"text":"To understand whether\nthere are any planets --"},{"time":71070,"text":"out there in our solar system or beyond --"},{"time":73372,"text":"that can support life,"},{"time":74854,"text":"the first step is to understand\nwhat life here requires."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78575,"text":"It turns out, of all of those\n8.7 million species,"},{"time":82162,"text":"life only needs three things."},{"time":85032,"text":"On one side, all life\non Earth needs energy."},{"time":87908,"text":"Complex life like us derives\nour energy from the sun,"},{"time":91417,"text":"but life deep underground\ncan get its energy"},{"time":93542,"text":"from things like chemical reactions."},{"time":95288,"text":"There are a number\nof different energy sources"},{"time":97463,"text":"available on all planets."},{"time":99400,"text":"On the other side,"},{"time":100580,"text":"all life needs food or nourishment."},{"time":103741,"text":"And this seems like a tall order,\nespecially if you want a succulent tomato."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108239,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109979,"text":"However, all life on Earth\nderives its nourishment"},{"time":113069,"text":"from only six chemical elements,"},{"time":115123,"text":"and these elements can be found\non any planetary body"},{"time":118151,"text":"in our solar system."},{"time":120537,"text":"So that leaves the thing\nin the middle as the tall pole,"},{"time":123788,"text":"the thing that's hardest to achieve."},{"time":125766,"text":"Not moose, but water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127682,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131285,"text":"Although moose would be pretty cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133103,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134285,"text":"And not frozen water, and not water\nin a gaseous state, but liquid water."},{"time":140748,"text":"This is what life needs\nto survive, all life."},{"time":143680,"text":"And many solar system bodies\ndon't have liquid water,"},{"time":147040,"text":"and so we don't look there."},{"time":148700,"text":"Other solar system bodies\nmight have abundant liquid water,"},{"time":151717,"text":"even more than Earth,"},{"time":153076,"text":"but it's trapped beneath an icy shell,"},{"time":155550,"text":"and so it's hard to access,\nit's hard to get to,"},{"time":157835,"text":"it's hard to even find out\nif there's any life there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161475,"text":"So that leaves a few bodies\nthat we should think about."},{"time":164494,"text":"So let's make the problem\nsimpler for ourselves."},{"time":166947,"text":"Let's think only about liquid water\non the surface of a planet."},{"time":170312,"text":"There are only three bodies\nto think about in our solar system,"},{"time":173292,"text":"with regard to liquid water\non the surface of a planet,"},{"time":175898,"text":"and in order of distance from the sun,\nit's: Venus, Earth and Mars."},{"time":181265,"text":"You want to have an atmosphere\nfor water to be liquid."},{"time":184661,"text":"You have to be very careful\nwith that atmosphere."},{"time":187063,"text":"You can't have too much atmosphere,\ntoo thick or too warm an atmosphere,"},{"time":190499,"text":"because then you end up\ntoo hot like Venus,"},{"time":193428,"text":"and you can't have liquid water."},{"time":195189,"text":"But if you have too little atmosphere\nand it's too thin and too cold,"},{"time":199166,"text":"you end up like Mars, too cold."},{"time":201865,"text":"So Venus is too hot, Mars is too cold,"},{"time":204364,"text":"and Earth is just right."},{"time":205552,"text":"You can look at these images behind me\nand you can see automatically"},{"time":209051,"text":"where life can survive\nin our solar system."},{"time":212296,"text":"It's a Goldilocks-type problem,"},{"time":213920,"text":"and it's so simple\nthat a child could understand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217452,"text":"However,"},{"time":219450,"text":"I'd like to remind you of two things"},{"time":222402,"text":"from the Goldilocks story\nthat we may not think about so often"},{"time":225380,"text":"but that I think are really relevant here."},{"time":228056,"text":"Number one:"},{"time":230311,"text":"if Mama Bear's bowl is too cold"},{"time":233833,"text":"when Goldilocks walks into the room,"},{"time":236642,"text":"does that mean it's always been too cold?"},{"time":239825,"text":"Or could it have been just right\nat some other time?"},{"time":243650,"text":"When Goldilocks walks into the room\ndetermines the answer"},{"time":247355,"text":"that we get in the story."},{"time":249114,"text":"And the same is true with planets."},{"time":250868,"text":"They're not static things. They change."},{"time":252918,"text":"They vary. They evolve."},{"time":254684,"text":"And atmospheres do the same."},{"time":256751,"text":"So let me give you an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258477,"text":"Here's one of my favorite\npictures of Mars."},{"time":260503,"text":"It's not the highest resolution image,\nit's not the sexiest image,"},{"time":263658,"text":"it's not the most recent image,"},{"time":265185,"text":"but it's an image that shows riverbeds\ncut into the surface of the planet;"},{"time":269320,"text":"riverbeds carved by flowing, liquid water;"},{"time":273515,"text":"riverbeds that take hundreds or thousands\nor tens of thousands of years to form."},{"time":278425,"text":"This can't happen on Mars today."},{"time":280067,"text":"The atmosphere of Mars today\nis too thin and too cold"},{"time":282572,"text":"for water to be stable as a liquid."},{"time":284737,"text":"This one image tells you\nthat the atmosphere of Mars changed,"},{"time":289109,"text":"and it changed in big ways."},{"time":291714,"text":"And it changed from a state\nthat we would define as habitable,"},{"time":296547,"text":"because the three requirements\nfor life were present long ago."},{"time":301049,"text":"Where did that atmosphere go"},{"time":303141,"text":"that allowed water\nto be liquid at the surface?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305985,"text":"Well, one idea is it escaped\naway to space."},{"time":309356,"text":"Atmospheric particles\ngot enough energy to break free"},{"time":312047,"text":"from the gravity of the planet,"},{"time":313724,"text":"escaping away to space, never to return."},{"time":316437,"text":"And this happens with all bodies\nwith atmospheres."},{"time":319149,"text":"Comets have tails"},{"time":320345,"text":"that are incredibly visible reminders\nof atmospheric escape."},{"time":323626,"text":"But Venus also has an atmosphere\nthat escapes with time,"},{"time":327059,"text":"and Mars and Earth as well."},{"time":328743,"text":"It's just a matter of degree\nand a matter of scale."},{"time":332092,"text":"So we'd like to figure out\nhow much escaped over time"},{"time":334792,"text":"so we can explain this transition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336932,"text":"How do atmospheres\nget their energy for escape?"},{"time":339567,"text":"How do particles get\nenough energy to escape?"},{"time":341722,"text":"There are two ways, if we're going\nto reduce things a little bit."},{"time":344931,"text":"Number one, sunlight."},{"time":346106,"text":"Light emitted from the sun can be absorbed\nby atmospheric particles"},{"time":349542,"text":"and warm the particles."},{"time":351280,"text":"Yes, I'm dancing, but they --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353412,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355693,"text":"Oh my God, not even at my wedding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357629,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359145,"text":"They get enough energy\nto escape and break free"},{"time":362172,"text":"from the gravity of the planet\njust by warming."},{"time":364696,"text":"A second way they can get energy\nis from the solar wind."},{"time":367882,"text":"These are particles, mass, material,\nspit out from the surface of the sun,"},{"time":372932,"text":"and they go screaming\nthrough the solar system"},{"time":375360,"text":"at 400 kilometers per second,"},{"time":377169,"text":"sometimes faster during solar storms,"},{"time":379787,"text":"and they go hurtling\nthrough interplanetary space"},{"time":382533,"text":"towards planets and their atmospheres,"},{"time":385003,"text":"and they may provide energy"},{"time":386652,"text":"for atmospheric particles\nto escape as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389182,"text":"This is something that I'm interested in,"},{"time":391175,"text":"because it relates to habitability."},{"time":393378,"text":"I mentioned that there were two things\nabout the Goldilocks story"},{"time":396534,"text":"that I wanted to bring to your attention\nand remind you about,"},{"time":399542,"text":"and the second one\nis a little bit more subtle."},{"time":401805,"text":"If Papa Bear's bowl is too hot,"},{"time":406180,"text":"and Mama Bear's bowl is too cold,"},{"time":411057,"text":"shouldn't Baby Bear's bowl be even colder"},{"time":415081,"text":"if we're following the trend?"},{"time":418195,"text":"This thing that you've accepted\nyour entire life,"},{"time":420531,"text":"when you think about it a little bit more,\nmay not be so simple."},{"time":424513,"text":"And of course, distance of a planet\nfrom the sun determines its temperature."},{"time":428565,"text":"This has to play into habitability."},{"time":430855,"text":"But maybe there are other things\nwe should be thinking about."},{"time":433809,"text":"Maybe it's the bowls themselves"},{"time":435449,"text":"that are also helping to determine\nthe outcome in the story,"},{"time":438529,"text":"what is just right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440765,"text":"I could talk to you about a lot\nof different characteristics"},{"time":443654,"text":"of these three planets"},{"time":444829,"text":"that may influence habitability,"},{"time":446422,"text":"but for selfish reasons related\nto my own research"},{"time":449040,"text":"and the fact that I'm standing up here\nholding the clicker and you're not --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452652,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453682,"text":"I would like to talk\nfor just a minute or two"},{"time":455815,"text":"about magnetic fields."},{"time":457715,"text":"Earth has one; Venus and Mars do not."},{"time":460825,"text":"Magnetic fields are generated\nin the deep interior of a planet"},{"time":463972,"text":"by electrically conducting\nchurning fluid material"},{"time":467713,"text":"that creates this big old magnetic field\nthat surrounds Earth."},{"time":470642,"text":"If you have a compass,\nyou know which way north is."},{"time":473062,"text":"Venus and Mars don't have that."},{"time":474580,"text":"If you have a compass on Venus and Mars,"},{"time":476518,"text":"congratulations, you're lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477938,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479865,"text":"Does this influence habitability?"},{"time":483175,"text":"Well, how might it?"},{"time":485024,"text":"Many scientists think\nthat a magnetic field of a planet"},{"time":487652,"text":"serves as a shield for the atmosphere,"},{"time":490071,"text":"deflecting solar wind particles\naround the planet"},{"time":493450,"text":"in a bit of a force field-type effect"},{"time":495289,"text":"having to do with electric charge\nof those particles."},{"time":498362,"text":"I like to think of it instead\nas a salad bar sneeze guard for planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502013,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504962,"text":"And yes, my colleagues\nwho watch this later will realize"},{"time":508367,"text":"this is the first time in the history\nof our community"},{"time":510935,"text":"that the solar wind has been\nequated with mucus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513238,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516978,"text":"OK, so the effect, then, is that Earth\nmay have been protected"},{"time":520477,"text":"for billions of years,"},{"time":521670,"text":"because we've had a magnetic field."},{"time":523544,"text":"Atmosphere hasn't been able to escape."},{"time":525747,"text":"Mars, on the other hand,\nhas been unprotected"},{"time":527878,"text":"because of its lack of magnetic field,"},{"time":529744,"text":"and over billions of years,"},{"time":531720,"text":"maybe enough atmosphere\nhas been stripped away"},{"time":533924,"text":"to account for a transition\nfrom a habitable planet"},{"time":536541,"text":"to the planet that we see today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539059,"text":"Other scientists think\nthat magnetic fields"},{"time":542072,"text":"may act more like the sails on a ship,"},{"time":544958,"text":"enabling the planet to interact\nwith more energy from the solar wind"},{"time":550019,"text":"than the planet would have been able\nto interact with by itself."},{"time":553315,"text":"The sails may gather energy\nfrom the solar wind."},{"time":555830,"text":"The magnetic field may gather\nenergy from the solar wind"},{"time":558520,"text":"that allows even more\natmospheric escape to happen."},{"time":561788,"text":"It's an idea that has to be tested,"},{"time":564066,"text":"but the effect and how it works"},{"time":565975,"text":"seems apparent."},{"time":567150,"text":"That's because we know"},{"time":568325,"text":"energy from the solar wind\nis being deposited into our atmosphere"},{"time":571424,"text":"here on Earth."},{"time":572599,"text":"That energy is conducted\nalong magnetic field lines"},{"time":575028,"text":"down into the polar regions,"},{"time":576400,"text":"resulting in incredibly beautiful aurora."},{"time":578560,"text":"If you've ever experienced them,\nit's magnificent."},{"time":581240,"text":"We know the energy is getting in."},{"time":583270,"text":"We're trying to measure\nhow many particles are getting out"},{"time":586327,"text":"and if the magnetic field\nis influencing this in any way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590722,"text":"So I've posed a problem for you here,"},{"time":593126,"text":"but I don't have a solution yet."},{"time":594696,"text":"We don't have a solution."},{"time":596702,"text":"But we're working on it.\nHow are we working on it?"},{"time":599083,"text":"Well, we've sent spacecraft\nto all three planets."},{"time":601405,"text":"Some of them are orbiting now,"},{"time":602905,"text":"including the MAVEN spacecraft\nwhich is currently orbiting Mars,"},{"time":606001,"text":"which I'm involved with\nand which is led here,"},{"time":609557,"text":"out of the University of Colorado."},{"time":611390,"text":"It's designed to measure\natmospheric escape."},{"time":614022,"text":"We have similar measurements\nfrom Venus and Earth."},{"time":616953,"text":"Once we have all our measurements,"},{"time":618642,"text":"we can combine all these together,\nand we can understand"},{"time":621541,"text":"how all three planets interact\nwith their space environment,"},{"time":624982,"text":"with the surroundings."},{"time":626168,"text":"And we can decide whether magnetic fields\nare important for habitability"},{"time":629714,"text":"or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630896,"text":"Once we have that answer,\nwhy should you care?"},{"time":633185,"text":"I mean, I care deeply ..."},{"time":636128,"text":"And financially as well, but deeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638158,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":640763,"text":"First of all, an answer to this question"},{"time":642705,"text":"will teach us more\nabout these three planets,"},{"time":644832,"text":"Venus, Earth and Mars,"},{"time":646016,"text":"not only about how they interact\nwith their environment today,"},{"time":648951,"text":"but how they were billions of years ago,"},{"time":650902,"text":"whether they were habitable\nlong ago or not."},{"time":652988,"text":"It will teach us about atmospheres"},{"time":654656,"text":"that surround us and that are close."},{"time":657127,"text":"But moreover, what we learn\nfrom these planets"},{"time":659335,"text":"can be applied to atmospheres everywhere,"},{"time":662485,"text":"including planets that we're now\nobserving around other stars."},{"time":665422,"text":"For example, the Kepler spacecraft,"},{"time":667201,"text":"which is built and controlled\nhere in Boulder,"},{"time":670433,"text":"has been observing\na postage stamp-sized region of the sky"},{"time":673742,"text":"for a couple years now,"},{"time":675013,"text":"and it's found thousands of planets --"},{"time":677265,"text":"in one postage stamp-sized\nregion of the sky"},{"time":680202,"text":"that we don't think is any different\nfrom any other part of the sky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684815,"text":"We've gone, in 20 years,"},{"time":686649,"text":"from knowing of zero planets\noutside of our solar system,"},{"time":690710,"text":"to now having so many,"},{"time":692487,"text":"that we don't know\nwhich ones to investigate first."},{"time":697269,"text":"Any lever will help."},{"time":700539,"text":"In fact, based on observations\nthat Kepler's taken"},{"time":704147,"text":"and other similar observations,"},{"time":706300,"text":"we now believe that,"},{"time":707493,"text":"of the 200 billion stars\nin the Milky Way galaxy alone,"},{"time":712786,"text":"on average, every star\nhas at least one planet."},{"time":718819,"text":"In addition to that,"},{"time":720346,"text":"estimates suggest there are somewhere\nbetween 40 billion and 100 billion"},{"time":726071,"text":"of those planets\nthat we would define as habitable"},{"time":731139,"text":"in just our galaxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734590,"text":"We have the observations of those planets,"},{"time":736651,"text":"but we just don't know\nwhich ones are habitable yet."},{"time":739159,"text":"It's a little bit like\nbeing trapped on a red spot --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":742789,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":743984,"text":"on a stage"},{"time":746178,"text":"and knowing that there are\nother worlds out there"},{"time":751042,"text":"and desperately wanting to know\nmore about them,"},{"time":755174,"text":"wanting to interrogate them and find out\nif maybe just one or two of them"},{"time":759132,"text":"are a little bit like you."},{"time":762244,"text":"You can't do that.\nYou can't go there, not yet."},{"time":764827,"text":"And so you have to use the tools\nthat you've developed around you"},{"time":768844,"text":"for Venus, Earth and Mars,"},{"time":770163,"text":"and you have to apply them\nto these other situations,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and hope that you're making\nreasonable inferences from the data,"},{"time":777720,"text":"and that you're going to be able\nto determine the best candidates"},{"time":780862,"text":"for habitable planets,\nand those that are not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784139,"text":"In the end, and for now, at least,"},{"time":786878,"text":"this is our red spot, right here."},{"time":790376,"text":"This is the only planet\nthat we know of that's habitable,"},{"time":793736,"text":"although very soon we may\ncome to know of more."},{"time":796951,"text":"But for now, this is\nthe only habitable planet,"},{"time":799711,"text":"and this is our red spot."},{"time":801976,"text":"I'm really glad we're here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804507,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805706,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}